Video Background Removal from Single Selection

Objective

The goal of this project is to enable a user to remove the background of a video, after having selected a subject in it. The tool should run on CPU, and should be easy to use (UI?).

Use case

This tool can be used for online content creators such as youtubers, to automatically remove the background of a video (such as a funny clip) and to use the output sequence (the interest subject over a green screen) in their own video.

Example

Let's take this video as an example.
The user should first draw a bounding box around the desired character on the first frame, like this:

The output should be the boy on a green screen, like this:

Note that the user should select the desired subject only once, and the tool should output the full video with the desired object on a green background.

Challenges

There are two main challenges:

  • Running the script on user's CPU, and compute fast;
  • Finding the selected object across all frames to allow the user to select it only once.

Ideas and tools we can use

MobileSAM for segmenting the desired object

MobileSAM allows for fast image segmentation, it is design to run on mobile devices, so it should be ok on cpu.

Use a lightweight object detector

We can use a fast object detector to get the bounding box of the subject in all frames, but it might be too heavy to run on cpu.

Use maths

With the hypothesis that the subject's location in a video frame is never too far away from its location in the previous frame, we could expand the initial bounding box to all 4 directions by a small delta, run the segmentation, and re-create a bounding box of the output mask to use for the next frame. This can work if the background is clear enough from the subject.

PerSAM for segmenting the same object in several images

This should help segmenting an object across several frames, but it is probably too heavy and cannot run on cpu.
